      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 1,
      "factorStatus": "not-assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Formal model-form uncertainty quantification comparing at least two turbulence closure models and two hemolysis constitutive laws; sensitivity documented.",
      "rationale": "Only SST k-omega turbulence model used; no alternative closure evaluated. Single Giersiepen-Wurzinger hemolysis law applied without comparison to Bludszuweit or modified power-law alternatives. Model-form uncertainty not quantified; epistemic gap at MRL 5."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Model inputs",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 5,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "All model input parameters characterised with probability distributions; Monte Carlo propagation of input uncertainty through hemolysis predictions with documented convergence.",
      "rationale": "Monte Carlo UQ performed with 500 samples propagating uncertainty in viscosity coefficients, inlet boundary conditions, and rotational speed. However, the rheology power-law coefficients are drawn from the 2025-Q3 dataset (dataVintage 2025-09-15), which predates the February 2026 model revision. Re-characterisation of these coefficients against the updated discretisation scheme is planned for Q2 2026 but has not been completed, leaving input uncertainty partially stale. Achieved level 2 against required level 5."
